{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Burgers","content":["Line a baking tray with baking paper.","Place garlic and onions in mixing bowl then chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add beef mince, tomato purée, chilli flakes, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce then mix <b>10 sec\/speed 6<b>.","Divide mixture into 4 balls then, using wet hands, flatten to form large patties (Ø 12-13 cm). Transfer to prepared tray, cover with cling film and chill in fridge for 30 minutes. Towards the end of this time, preheat oven to 190°C."]},{"title":"Sweet Potato Wedges","content":["Spray a large baking tray with oil. Arrange sweet potato wedges on prepared tray, sprinkle with garlic powder, paprika, salt and pepper then toss to coat. Bake for 40 minutes (190°C). With 15 minutes remaining, place chilled patties in oven too and bake for 12-15 minutes (190°C) until cooked, flipping halfway through."]},{"title":"Assembly","content":["Divide lettuce and tomatoes between buns then place a cooked beef patty on each. Top with cheese, onion and ketchup. Serve with sweet potato wedges."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Burgers","content":["2 garlic cloves","100 g onions, quartered","400 g beef mince, 5% fat, broken in pieces","1 Tbsp tomato purée","½ tsp dried chilli flakes","1 tsp fine sea salt","¼ tsp ground black pepper","2 tsp Worcestershire sauce"]},{"title":"Sweet Potato Wedges","content":["cooking spray, any oil","3 sweet potatoes (approx. 180 g each), cut lengthways into 8 wedges","½ tsp garlic powder","½ tsp smoked paprika","½ tsp fine sea salt","¼ tsp ground black pepper"]},{"title":"Assembly","content":["4 burger buns, seeded or wholemeal","4 green lettuce leaves (e.g. iceberg, baby cos)","2 beef tomatoes, sliced (1 cm)","4 cheese slices, reduced fat","1 red onion, sliced (5 mm)","tomato ketchup, to taste, for topping"]}],"id":"r424069","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-JTUnVAnF3Is\/XZQFyu6-ouI\/AAAAAAAAb24\/7cDf1-0-tRYUiB5